fields.description:
Implement wait action that blocks until agents reach final state.

## Deliverables
- src/agent/wait.ts (or integrate into control.ts)

## Design (matching codex wait handler)
```typescript
async function wait(options: {
  control: AgentControl;
  ids: AgentId[];
  timeoutMs: number;  // default 30_000, max 300_000
  signal?: AbortSignal;
}): Promise<WaitResult>;

interface WaitResult {
  status: Record<AgentId, Status>;
  timedOut: boolean;
}
```

## Behavior
1. Subscribe to status for all ids
2. If any already final → return immediately with those
3. Otherwise wait until first reaches final OR timeout
4. Return status map + timed_out flag

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Returns immediately if any agent already in final state
- [ ] Waits for first agent to reach final state
- [ ] Respects timeout (default 30s, max 300s)
- [ ] timedOut=true if no agent finished before timeout
- [ ] Status map includes all requested ids
- [ ] Missing agents return status 'not_found' (or error)
- [ ] Handles concurrent status changes correctly
- [ ] Cleans up subscriptions on completion/timeout
- [ ] Respects abort signal
